    "explanation": "Diagram 1 focuses on the internal workings of the Nginx server and its interaction with FastCGI functions, depicting how request handlers and location directives trigger the execution of C/C++ functions. Diagram 2 provides a higher-level overview of the architecture, starting with the client and detailing the flow of requests and responses between the client, web server (specifically Nginx), and the FastCGI application. While both diagrams feature Nginx, Diagram 1 dives into the specifics of its configuration and execution of functions, whereas Diagram 2 presents a more abstract view of the application's overall structure and data flow. Diagram 1 uses a more function-centric viewpoint, detailing the handler mechanisms and function calls involved. Diagram 2 emphasizes the application layers and their communication, from client interaction to FastCGI processing. The diagrams share the concept of FastCGI integration with Nginx, however they explore it from different angles of abstraction."
